DURBAN – Barely a year after prominent businessman Morgan Naidoo was found murdered along the N3 highway, his 27-year-old daughter, living in Johannesburg, was found dead in her Sandton apartment on Sunday. Lerusha Naidoo’s death comes shortly after her father, was found murdered last year, his murder remains unsolved. Lerusha, an honours graduate, who had been working as a consultant for IQ Business in Sandton was found in her apartment on Sunday morning when her friend raised the alarm after failing to make contact with her. Her lifeless body was found hanging in a clothing cupboard. Police are questioning two people of interest after it emerged that she had entertained guests at her apartment on Saturday night. It is believed a friend tried contacting her on Sunday and then went to the flat to look for Lerusha after repeated calls went unanswered.  Upon arrival at the flat, the friend found that Lerusha’s car was in its parking bay, but there was no answer when the friend knocked at her door and called out for her.  The flat door was eventually forced open and Naidoo’s body was discovered in the cupboard. Investigations continue. Lerusha and her dad Morgan Naidoo – he was found murdered barely a year ago. Photo: Supplied Last year, her father went missing for four days, and was found murdered at the bridge at the Lynnfield Park N3 on-ramp. He was blindfolded with his hands tied behind back and he had sustained three gunshot wounds. Morgan, who lived in Hayfields, Pietermaritzburg, hailed from a prominent business family and was himself a successful businessman with various retail interests in the Midlands.